I'm not six years old.
Give me that.

15:42.898 --> 15:44.769
- [sighs]

15:44.813 --> 15:48.948
Gotta say,
writing's not your forte.

15:48.991 --> 15:52.560
Stick to sculpture.
- Fuck you.

15:52.603 --> 15:55.215
- You should just call it
"Devon, Devon, Devon."

15:55.258 --> 15:57.217
[laughs]

15:57.260 --> 15:58.566
- Shut up.

16:00.220 --> 16:03.440
- You know, I have a queer kid.

16:05.616 --> 16:07.488
- You have a kid?

16:07.531 --> 16:09.925
- Genderfluid.

16:09.969 --> 16:13.929
- And you're cool with it?

16:13.973 --> 16:16.845
- I'm not a monster, Jake.

16:16.888 --> 16:19.152
- No, you are.
You killed Annie!

16:19.195 --> 16:21.067
- Come on, man.
Think.

16:21.110 --> 16:23.591
Why would I kill Annie?

16:23.634 --> 16:28.248
You and me, we only kill people
who have it coming.

16:28.291 --> 16:30.728
- No.
No, I don't kill anyone.

16:30.772 --> 16:33.035
And I don't want you
to kill anyone else.

16:33.079 --> 16:36.865
- It wasn't me!
Accidents happen, Jake.

16:36.908 --> 16:41.087
More often than murder,
and way more often than murders

16:41.130 --> 16:43.567
committed by
supernaturally-possessed dolls.

16:43.611 --> 16:46.614
That's just basic math.

16:46.657 --> 16:48.616
And let me remind you

16:48.659 --> 16:52.141
that I could have killed
anybody in this house

16:52.185 --> 16:56.537
during the last week
at any time,

16:56.580 --> 16:58.756
including you.

17:01.803 --> 17:04.066
- So why haven't you?
- I told you.

17:04.110 --> 17:06.938
I'm trying to help you.

17:06.982 --> 17:09.115
Look around, kid!

17:09.158 --> 17:12.205
Take a good look
at where you are.

17:12.248 --> 17:15.773
A long way from that shithole
you used to live in

17:15.817 --> 17:20.126
with that shitheel who liked
using you for a punching bag.

17:20.169 --> 17:23.085
I'm the one friend
you got, Jake.

17:23.129 --> 17:24.913
And I'm telling you,

17:24.956 --> 17:29.004
I did not kill
the damn housekeeper.

17:29.048 --> 17:32.660
I got my sights
set on bigger game.

17:32.703 --> 17:34.575
- Chucky, no.

17:34.618 --> 17:38.013
- You of all people should know

17:38.057 --> 17:42.148
some people deserve to die.

17:42.191 --> 17:45.151
<i>[eerie music]</i>

17:45.194 --> 17:51.592
<i>♪ </i>

17:51.635 --> 17:54.638
- You heard what they said.
It was an accident.

17:54.682 --> 17:56.814
- No, what I heard was that

17:56.858 --> 17:59.861
it was
an astronomical coincidence,

17:59.904 --> 18:01.689
the chances of which
actually happening

18:01.732 --> 18:03.343
are about a billion to one.

18:03.386 --> 18:05.780
- We watched him grow up.

18:05.823 --> 18:08.739
He's not a violent kid.
He's just traumatized.

18:08.783 --> 18:10.828
- We're all traumatized.

18:10.872 --> 18:14.136
I mean, are we even qualified
to look after a boy like this?

18:14.180 --> 18:15.964
- A boy like what?

18:16.007 --> 18:18.880
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

18:18.923 --> 18:20.708
- Okay.

18:20.751 --> 18:24.190
You yourself said many times
that you were worried

18:24.233 --> 18:26.192
that your brother
was a bad influence on him,

18:26.235 --> 18:28.063
especially after Mary died.

18:28.107 --> 18:32.720
Logan, we don't have a clue
what's going on in his head.

18:32.763 --> 18:34.809
- We could say the same
for Junior.

18:34.852 --> 18:37.290
No one knows what's going on
inside their heads.

18:37.333 --> 18:39.205
Bree, they're teenagers.

18:39.248 --> 18:41.381
- You know exactly
what Junior is thinking,

18:41.424 --> 18:43.731
24 hours a day,
consciously or unconsciously,

18:43.774 --> 18:45.646
and it's pleasing you.

18:45.689 --> 18:47.256
- You say that
like it's a bad thing.

18:47.300 --> 18:49.215
- You're pushing him
too hard, Logan.

18:49.258 --> 18:50.912
I'm worried about him.

18:50.955 --> 18:52.783
- Bree, I'm just trying
to help him succeed.

18:52.827 --> 18:55.351
<i>♪ </i>

18:55.395 --> 18:58.354
[shower running]

18:58.398 --> 19:05.274
<i>♪ </i>

19:34.999 --> 19:41.963
<i>♪ </i>

19:49.275 --> 19:51.146
- What the hell are you doing?

19:53.453 --> 19:55.194
- Was gonna ask you
the same thing.

19:58.022 --> 20:02.288
<i>♪ </i>

20:02.331 --> 20:04.986
- Wait, no, that's--
that's not--

20:05.029 --> 20:06.727
- Stay away from her.

20:06.770 --> 20:08.990
- I didn't do that.

20:09.033 --> 20:15.866
<i>♪ </i>

20:19.348 --> 20:21.002
What the hell?

20:21.045 --> 20:24.788
Chucky, I told you, back off.

20:24.832 --> 20:27.965
I'm not letting you.

20:28.009 --> 20:29.880
What are you gonna do about it?

20:29.924 --> 20:31.186
[heavy thud]
Ugh!

20:35.625 --> 20:38.498
<i>[spooky dramatic music]</i>

20:38.976 --> 20:43.285
<i>♪ </i>

20:43.329 --> 20:45.722
- I'm sorry.
Did you say dishwasher?

20:45.766 --> 20:48.551
Jesus.
What did Evan say?

20:48.595 --> 20:50.727
Look.

20:50.771 --> 20:52.381
Okay.

20:52.425 --> 20:54.253
Was there any press this time?

20:56.342 --> 20:57.734
Good. Let's keep it that way.

20:57.778 --> 20:59.301
Okay, I've got to go.
Got to go.

20:59.345 --> 21:01.390
Take this.
Look. Look, look, look.

21:03.349 --> 21:07.004
Oh, honey, that's so good.

21:07.048 --> 21:10.573
I'm speechless.
It's incredible.

21:10.617 --> 21:12.271
All that detail
after seeing him

21:12.314 --> 21:13.663
for, what, five minutes?

21:13.707 --> 21:14.969
- Eidetic memory.
- Yeah.

21:16.710 --> 21:18.755
- Baby, can you
remember his name?

21:18.799 --> 21:22.498
- Chucky.
- Yes, that's right.

21:22.542 --> 21:25.501
Caroline, would you maybe
like to meet Chucky sometime?

21:25.545 --> 21:27.677
I bet your sister
could make that happen.

21:27.721 --> 21:29.288
- What?

21:29.331 --> 21:31.594
- Oh, no, I'd be too scared.

21:31.638 --> 21:34.771
- Why, honey?
- What if he doesn't like me?

21:35.946 --> 21:37.687
- Why are you encouraging this?

21:37.731 --> 21:39.820
That thing belongs
to Jake Wheeler.

21:39.863 --> 21:41.343
And I'm sorry,
but did you not hear him

21:41.387 --> 21:43.345
talking shit about me
at the talent show?

21:43.389 --> 21:46.000
- Honey, you're overreacting.
It was a joke!

21:46.043 --> 21:47.958
In a way,
you should be flattered.

21:48.002 --> 21:50.047
The whole thing
was all about you.

21:50.091 --> 21:52.398
- Oh, Dad,
that's fucking awesome.

21:52.441 --> 21:54.704
I'm just so thrilled
you all found it so amusing.

21:54.748 --> 21:57.533
As usual, you both totally
ignore what's going on with me.

21:57.577 --> 21:59.709
It's called bullying.
He's a bully.

21:59.753 --> 22:01.624
- Who's a bully?
Chucky?

22:01.668 --> 22:04.714
- No.
No, honey, he's not.

22:04.758 --> 22:07.717
- Give me a break.

22:07.761 --> 22:09.066
- Will you take a look at this?

22:09.110 --> 22:10.416
Here, sweetie.

22:14.811 --> 22:16.422
- It's hideous.

22:18.424 --> 22:20.643
- Lexy, your sister has a gift,

22:20.687 --> 22:22.384
and she's better at this
than you've ever been

22:22.428 --> 22:23.733
at anything
in your entire life.

22:23.777 --> 22:25.082
- Michelle!
- No, I'm sorry.

22:25.126 --> 22:27.520
I just can't take
her attitude anymore.

22:27.563 --> 22:29.739
It breaks my heart.

22:29.783 --> 22:32.655
Your sister adores you.

22:32.699 --> 22:34.353
- She barely knows I exist.

22:34.396 --> 22:36.355
And it's obvious
neither do you guys.

22:36.398 --> 22:38.095
- Where do you think
you're going?

22:38.139 --> 22:39.880
- To get ready
for Oliver's party.

22:39.923 --> 22:43.013
- No, you're taking your sister
trick-or-treating.

22:43.057 --> 22:45.581
- I have a costume.
It was expensive.

22:45.625 --> 22:47.409
- And I have
the Hacky Halloween Ball,

22:47.453 --> 22:49.106
and your father
has to be with me.

22:49.150 --> 22:50.717
- "The Daily Voice"
is doing a story

22:50.760 --> 22:52.936
on Hackensack's
very first first husband.

22:52.980 --> 22:55.417
- Besides, Dr. Mixter
says that Halloween

22:55.461 --> 22:58.986
is the perfect opportunity
for you girls to bond.

22:59.029 --> 23:00.422
- Bond?

23:00.466 --> 23:01.771
She doesn't even like
to be touched.

23:01.815 --> 23:04.774
<i>[eerie music]</i>

23:04.818 --> 23:10.954
<i>♪ </i>

23:12.782 --> 23:16.003
- Annie?
Their housekeeper?

23:16.046 --> 23:17.700
What happened?

23:17.744 --> 23:20.703
- An accident.
Another accident.

23:24.490 --> 23:25.839
- She used to make popsicles
when we were

23:25.882 --> 23:27.754
at Junior's after school.

23:29.625 --> 23:31.497
She was really nice.

23:31.540 --> 23:33.847
- I know.
It's very sad.

23:35.631 --> 23:38.112
Look, I have to head back
to the office for a while.

23:38.155 --> 23:39.983
Did you eat anything?

23:40.027 --> 23:42.421
- I'll have something
at the party.

23:42.464 --> 23:43.770
- Junior going?

23:43.813 --> 23:45.946
- Yep.
Lexy too.

23:45.989 --> 23:47.513
- What about Jake?

23:50.646 --> 23:52.474
- How would I know?

23:52.518 --> 23:54.476
It's not like we hang
in the same crowd.

23:54.520 --> 23:56.826
- Even now that he's
living at Junior's?

23:58.045 --> 23:59.046
- No.

24:03.137 --> 24:06.532
- Dev, did Jake ever say
anything about his father?

24:06.575 --> 24:09.186
About his father hurting him?

24:09.230 --> 24:11.624
- What do you mean?

24:11.667 --> 24:14.714
- Like, maybe because he's gay?

24:17.064 --> 24:19.414
- How would I know?
- I don't know.

24:21.677 --> 24:24.071
- Mom, what are
we talking about?

24:27.553 --> 24:30.512
- I'm just doing my job.

24:30.556 --> 24:33.036
- As a mom or a cop?

24:33.080 --> 24:35.909
- A bit of both, I guess.

24:35.952 --> 24:38.607
[chuckles]

24:38.651 --> 24:42.045
Have fun at the party.
- Later.

24:42.089 --> 24:45.048
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

24:45.092 --> 24:51.968
<i>♪ </i>

24:54.884 --> 24:57.844
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

24:57.887 --> 25:04.894
<i>♪ </i>

25:04.938 --> 25:07.549
[indistinct chatter]

25:07.593 --> 25:14.034
<i>♪ </i>

25:14.077 --> 25:15.949
[phone chimes]

25:29.963 --> 25:36.883
<i>♪ </i>

25:43.803 --> 25:45.108
- Hey, hang on, hang on.

25:45.152 --> 25:48.068
You're not still going
to the party, are you?

25:48.111 --> 25:50.157
- Why not?

25:50.200 --> 25:51.767
- Well, I just thought
after everything

25:51.811 --> 25:53.073
that happened today,
you'd want to spend

25:53.116 --> 25:55.902
some time with your family.

25:55.945 --> 25:58.600
- I just need to get
out of the house, okay?

25:58.644 --> 26:00.733
- Wow.

26:00.776 --> 26:03.953
You look great.
Are those my medals?

26:03.997 --> 26:06.086
- Yeah.
- Wow.

26:08.131 --> 26:09.611
what's Lexy going as?

26:09.655 --> 26:12.309
- It's a surprise.
- Oh.

26:12.353 --> 26:15.138
You know, I think you two
make a terrific couple.

26:15.182 --> 26:17.140
- Thank you.
Uber's here.

26:17.184 --> 26:18.794
I gotta go.
See you guys later.

26:18.838 --> 26:19.969
- Oh, what about Jake?

26:26.976 --> 26:29.022
- Hey, Jake, your Uber's here!

26:34.854 --> 26:36.159
Jake?

26:48.955 --> 26:52.001
Wow, Jake.
You look incredible.

26:52.045 --> 26:54.830
- That looks so real.
- Yeah.

26:54.874 --> 26:57.267
Who you supposed to be, though?

26:57.311 --> 26:59.748
- Victim of circumstances.

26:59.792 --> 27:02.098
- Huh. That's great, Jake.

27:02.142 --> 27:04.013
I think Junior
already took off.

27:04.057 --> 27:06.233
You want a ride?

27:06.276 --> 27:08.801
- Actually, I changed my mind.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.890
I don't think I'm up
for a party tonight.

27:10.933 --> 27:12.761
- I understand.
- Okay.

27:15.198 --> 27:17.026
- Got some stuff to do
in my room.

27:22.902 --> 27:24.207
Shit!
[door slams]

27:24.251 --> 27:25.644
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27:25.687 --> 27:27.820
Where is he?

27:27.863 --> 27:29.386
Did Junior take him?

27:29.430 --> 27:30.866
- What are you talking about?

27:30.910 --> 27:33.782
- Chucky.
He's gone.

27:38.744 --> 27:41.660
[indistinct chatter]

27:42.486 --> 27:44.706
<i>[spooky dramatic music]</i>

27:44.750 --> 27:46.708
<i>♪ </i>

27:46.752 --> 27:48.710
- [laughs]

27:48.754 --> 27:55.848
<i>♪ </i>

27:55.891 --> 27:59.199
Jesus Christ, you all look
like a bunch of damn idiots.

27:59.242 --> 28:01.157
[doorbell rings]
all: Trick or treat!

28:01.201 --> 28:02.724
- [laughing]
Oh.

28:02.768 --> 28:06.859
Aren't you girls a little
mature for this type of thing?

28:06.902 --> 28:09.688
You know, when I was your age,

28:09.731 --> 28:11.385
I was high as a kite.

28:11.428 --> 28:12.821
You have a good time.

28:12.865 --> 28:14.301
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

28:14.344 --> 28:17.217
- Oh.
- Hi. I'm Chucky.

28:17.260 --> 28:18.740
Want to play?

28:18.784 --> 28:21.743
- Oh, Hello Kitty!
[chuckles]

28:21.787 --> 28:23.745
- If you tell me
what I need to know,

28:23.789 --> 28:25.529
I'll give you a treat.

28:25.573 --> 28:27.749
- Oh, well,
what do you need to know?

28:27.793 --> 28:30.796
- I'm looking for a party!
- A party.

28:30.839 --> 28:33.755
Aren't you a little young
for that type of thing?

28:33.799 --> 28:37.585
- If you don't tell me,
you might just get a trick.

28:37.628 --> 28:40.414
- Well, I don't think
that will be necessary.

28:40.457 --> 28:41.763
Let me think.

28:41.807 --> 28:43.634
Oh, I know.

28:43.678 --> 28:46.159
The Haydens have
a big Halloween party

28:46.202 --> 28:47.421
every year.

28:47.464 --> 28:49.771
Well, at least
their son Oliver does.

28:49.815 --> 28:51.599
You can hear it from here.
- Oliver.

28:51.642 --> 28:53.775
- It's just two blocks over
on Claremont Street.

28:53.819 --> 28:57.474
- Thanks, lady.
[hums melody]

28:59.215 --> 29:01.217
Here's your treat.

29:01.261 --> 29:03.437
- Ooh, thank you.

29:05.656 --> 29:07.920
- [laughs]

29:07.963 --> 29:10.879
<i>[heavy techno music]</i>

29:10.923 --> 29:14.883
<i>♪ </i>

29:14.927 --> 29:16.580
- Where's Lexy?

29:16.624 --> 29:18.278
- Up there.

29:18.321 --> 29:25.198
<i>♪ </i>

29:36.339 --> 29:37.863
- Hey.
- Hey.

29:39.473 --> 29:41.823
- Are you--you okay?

29:43.520 --> 29:47.220
- Of course I'm okay.
How else would I be?

29:52.703 --> 29:55.402
- You know that I can't.
- Why not?

29:55.445 --> 29:56.795
Daddy's not here to stop you.

29:58.971 --> 30:01.843
- Do me a favor.

30:01.887 --> 30:04.977
Be careful with Jake, okay?

30:05.020 --> 30:07.718
He's got issues.

30:07.762 --> 30:10.504
- I'm not afraid of Jake.

30:10.547 --> 30:12.854
His creepy doll
just creeps me the fuck out.

30:15.901 --> 30:18.773
- Me too.
- So...

30:20.819 --> 30:22.951
- Whatever happens,
I'll protect you.

30:24.953 --> 30:28.827
- Junior Wheeler, my hero.

30:28.870 --> 30:30.524
Will you catch me if I fall?

30:30.567 --> 30:33.788
- Lex, I'm serious.

30:33.832 --> 30:34.920
- Sad but true.

30:37.748 --> 30:40.490
- Would you catch me?

30:42.405 --> 30:43.798
- What do you think?

30:46.409 --> 30:48.672
- Probably not.

30:51.937 --> 30:53.895
So what are you supposed to be?

30:55.505 --> 30:57.986
- Just you wait.

30:58.030 --> 30:59.422
- What if I can't wait?

31:01.990 --> 31:05.341
- Well, then come on, Jun-Jun.

31:05.385 --> 31:06.908
Come to Daddy.

31:06.952 --> 31:09.911
<i>[Electric Youth's
"Modern Fears"] </i>

31:09.955 --> 31:11.304
<i>[dreamy pop music]</i>

31:11.347 --> 31:13.697
<i>- ♪ They can </i>

31:13.741 --> 31:17.745
<i>♪ Say what they say </i>

31:17.788 --> 31:20.966
<i>♪ But you need a heart </i>

31:21.009 --> 31:23.011
<i>♪ To have heart like you do </i>

31:23.055 --> 31:26.580
<i>♪ </i>

31:26.623 --> 31:29.322
<i>♪ You're too </i>

31:29.365 --> 31:32.629
<i>♪ You're too careful </i>

31:32.673 --> 31:34.936
<i>♪ To truly not care </i>

31:34.980 --> 31:36.546
- Have you seen Lexy?

31:36.590 --> 31:39.593
- Why is everybody
looking for Lexy?

31:39.636 --> 31:41.987
- [scoffs]
Let's go.

31:42.030 --> 31:43.771
- Hey.
Where's your doll?

31:43.814 --> 31:45.512
- We want Chucky.

31:45.555 --> 31:47.470
- Chucky?
You've seen Chucky?

31:47.514 --> 31:49.908
- Dude, you lost your doll?

31:49.951 --> 31:52.432
- Jake.

31:52.475 --> 31:55.826
- Oh, Devon.
You look great.

31:55.870 --> 31:57.393
- I didn't think
you were coming.

31:57.437 --> 31:58.829
It's cool that you're here.

32:00.483 --> 32:03.008
- I've gotta find Lexy.
- Is something wrong?

32:03.051 --> 32:06.489
- I just--I've gotta find her.
- Why?

32:06.533 --> 32:08.448
- I just--I need
to make sure she's okay.

32:08.491 --> 32:10.972
- Why do you care?

32:11.016 --> 32:12.452
- Oh, Oliver,
have you seen Lexy?

32:12.495 --> 32:13.932
- Who?
- Lexy.

32:13.975 --> 32:15.455
- Oh, yeah, she's in there.

32:19.633 --> 32:21.417
- Wait.

32:21.461 --> 32:23.637
- Seven minutes in hell.

32:23.680 --> 32:26.640
[all chanting]
Hell, hell, hell, hell, hell!

32:26.683 --> 32:28.598
Hell, hell, hell, hell,
hell, hell, hell, hell!

32:28.642 --> 32:31.514
[all cheer]

32:32.385 --> 32:33.342
- Jake.

32:36.041 --> 32:39.348
Jake, your eye.
It looks so real.

32:42.569 --> 32:45.006
- Oliver, let us out.

32:45.050 --> 32:46.529
Oliver, let us out!

32:46.573 --> 32:49.445
<i>[blood splattering]</i>

32:51.534 --> 32:53.797
- You're good at this, Chucky.

32:53.841 --> 32:56.844
- You too, Caroline.
You got potential.

32:56.887 --> 32:59.803
I always say
killing's good, clean fun

32:59.847 --> 33:01.501
for the whole family.

33:01.544 --> 33:04.112
You can kill the housekeeper.

33:04.156 --> 33:06.897
You can kill the babysitter.

33:06.941 --> 33:09.770
You can even kill your sister.

33:09.813 --> 33:12.686
- Mommy says
real killing is bad.

33:12.729 --> 33:15.689
- Yeah, well,
Mommy's full of shit.

33:15.732 --> 33:19.867
- Mommy says
it isn't nice to swear.

33:19.910 --> 33:22.522
- Mommy's working
her way up my list

33:22.565 --> 33:25.090
pretty fucking quick.

33:25.133 --> 33:27.570
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

33:27.614 --> 33:28.876
<i>[game character screams]</i>

33:28.919 --> 33:30.747
But first things first, kid.

33:32.097 --> 33:34.577
where's Lexy?

33:34.621 --> 33:38.494
- Probably kissing
Junior somewhere.

33:38.538 --> 33:41.845
- Well, at least she's gonna
die doing what she loves.

33:41.889 --> 33:47.721
<i>♪ </i>

33:52.987 --> 33:56.077
- You're not doing it right.
- I haven't done anything yet.

33:56.817 --> 33:57.339
- No duh. I noticed.

34:00.168 --> 34:02.083
Just--you know what?
Forget it.

34:02.127 --> 34:04.085
- We can hug.
- Yeah.

34:04.129 --> 34:07.567
- [laughs]
What are you, my mom?

34:07.610 --> 34:09.569
- Tell me
what you want me to do.

34:09.612 --> 34:12.224
- Well, you're supposed
to know what to do.

34:12.267 --> 34:14.313
- [grunting]

34:14.356 --> 34:17.664
- Stop.
Did you feel that?

34:17.707 --> 34:19.361
- Did you do something?

34:19.405 --> 34:21.059
- The mattress moved.

34:21.102 --> 34:23.322
- [grunting]

34:27.413 --> 34:30.068
- "We can hug."
- I didn't mean it like that.

34:30.111 --> 34:32.635
- Hug.

34:32.679 --> 34:35.334
- What are you two
doing in here?

34:35.377 --> 34:37.162
- Absolutely nothing.

34:39.468 --> 34:41.470
- Lexy, wait.

34:41.514 --> 34:44.169
<i>[eerie music]</i>

34:44.212 --> 34:47.215
- Oy.

34:47.259 --> 34:50.610
- How much time?
- 30 seconds to go.

34:51.698 --> 34:54.483
- What's going on with you?
- Nothing.

34:54.527 --> 34:56.398
- It's not nothing.
I can tell.

34:56.442 --> 34:58.487
- If I told you,
you wouldn't believe me.

34:58.531 --> 35:01.534
- Yes, I would.
- Why?

35:01.577 --> 35:04.450
- I just don't think
you'd lie to me.

35:07.148 --> 35:08.410
<i>♪ </i>

35:08.454 --> 35:10.238
- Leave my friends alone!

35:10.282 --> 35:13.589
<i>♪ </i>

35:13.633 --> 35:16.462
- Dude, you have
a serious doll problem.

35:18.246 --> 35:20.770
- If you only knew.

35:20.814 --> 35:22.294
- [imitating kissing noises]

35:22.337 --> 35:24.774
- Kissy-kissy.
- Lovebirds.

35:24.818 --> 35:27.690
[all cheering]

35:29.475 --> 35:31.564
- Is he a good kisser?

35:31.607 --> 35:33.609
[people chanting]
Lexy, Lexy, Lexy, Lexy!

35:33.653 --> 35:35.176
- Lexy is here.
- Move.

35:35.220 --> 35:36.743
- I just don't get
why you care.

35:36.786 --> 35:40.616
[people chanting]
Lexy, Lexy, Lexy, Lexy, Lexy!

35:40.660 --> 35:44.403
- Oh, oh, oh!

35:44.446 --> 35:46.318
[laughter]

35:46.361 --> 35:48.146
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

35:48.189 --> 35:51.105
[grunting]

35:53.455 --> 35:57.807
<i>♪ </i>

35:57.851 --> 36:00.810
[grunting]

36:00.854 --> 36:03.378
<i>♪ </i>

36:03.422 --> 36:05.380
[grunting]

36:05.424 --> 36:08.427
[laughter]

36:08.470 --> 36:12.300
<i>♪ </i>

36:12.344 --> 36:13.301
[electricity crackles]

36:13.345 --> 36:15.216
<i>♪ </i>

36:15.260 --> 36:16.435
[electricity crackles]

36:16.478 --> 36:21.744
<i>♪ </i>

36:21.788 --> 36:24.747
[grunting]

36:24.791 --> 36:26.445
- What?

36:26.488 --> 36:29.796
<i>♪ </i>

36:29.839 --> 36:31.406
- She's my dad.

36:35.584 --> 36:40.763
<i>♪ </i>

36:40.807 --> 36:42.330
- I'm sorry.
That's so fucked up.

36:42.374 --> 36:43.679
- It's not your fault.

36:43.723 --> 36:46.291
- Okay, I don't know
what Lexy's problem is.

36:46.334 --> 36:48.206
- I can't let her
get away with this.

36:48.249 --> 36:51.513
- You don't have to do that.
- Yes, I do.

36:51.557 --> 36:54.212
I'm gonna show her
what it's like to get hurt.

36:54.255 --> 36:55.691
- [muffled]
It was this terrible

36:55.735 --> 36:58.346
redheaded child.

36:58.390 --> 37:01.436
I hold him responsible.

37:01.480 --> 37:04.352
- I'm sorry.
I didn't get that.

37:04.396 --> 37:08.704
- I said it was
this horrible redheaded child.

37:08.748 --> 37:11.359
I hold him responsible.

37:11.403 --> 37:12.882
- Red hair?
- Yes.

37:12.926 --> 37:15.711
Hello Kitty mask

37:15.755 --> 37:20.281
with tennis shoes
and denim overalls.

37:20.325 --> 37:23.632
They had something
stitched on them.

37:23.676 --> 37:26.722
- Do you remember
what it said on the overalls?

37:26.766 --> 37:30.552
- "Good gay."
"Good guy."

37:30.596 --> 37:34.295
- Red hair.
- Yeah, exactly.

37:34.339 --> 37:35.818
Does he sound familiar?

37:35.862 --> 37:37.559
- Yes, he does.

37:37.603 --> 37:40.519
<i>[spooky dramatic music]</i>

37:40.562 --> 37:41.781
<i>♪ </i>

37:41.824 --> 37:44.174
- I don't want to go!

37:44.218 --> 37:46.307
- Caroline, come on.

37:46.351 --> 37:48.440
- I have a new friend.

37:48.483 --> 37:49.658
- That's great, Care,

37:49.702 --> 37:52.270
but we still
have to get out of here.

37:52.313 --> 37:55.534
Come on.
- My new friend!

37:55.577 --> 37:57.797
- Care, I don't know what
you're talking about, but--

37:57.840 --> 38:02.280
<i>♪ </i>

38:02.323 --> 38:03.542
What?

38:03.585 --> 38:07.285
<i>♪ </i>

38:07.328 --> 38:08.808
- Aha.
- No!

38:08.851 --> 38:10.723
- Jake, wait!

38:10.766 --> 38:12.638
- [sighs]

38:12.681 --> 38:15.597
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

38:15.641 --> 38:20.559
<i>♪ </i>

38:20.602 --> 38:23.257
- His creepy doll
just creeps me the fuck out.

38:35.922 --> 38:39.404
<i>♪ </i>

38:39.447 --> 38:41.623
- How you doing?

38:41.667 --> 38:44.539
- Not good.

38:44.583 --> 38:47.847
- Look,
sorry about the eye, kid.

38:47.890 --> 38:50.676
I promise
I will never do that again.

38:54.375 --> 38:55.811
- Heard that before.

38:55.855 --> 39:00.425
<i>♪ </i>

39:00.468 --> 39:03.341
- That was some party.

39:03.384 --> 39:04.690
- It sucked.

39:04.733 --> 39:07.345
- Like I said before, Jake,

39:07.388 --> 39:11.479
some people
just deserve to die.

39:11.523 --> 39:13.525
<i>♪ </i>

39:13.568 --> 39:15.483
Look at the world.

39:15.527 --> 39:18.921
It's the Super Bowl
of slaughter.

39:18.965 --> 39:22.490
And you can't just sit
in the stands, you know?

39:22.534 --> 39:26.407
We all gotta get out there
and get in the game.

39:26.451 --> 39:30.368
It's kill or be killed.

39:30.411 --> 39:33.675
Whose team
do you want to be on?

39:33.719 --> 39:38.419
Because sooner or later,
everybody's gotta choose.

39:38.463 --> 39:41.422
<i>[eerie music]</i>

39:41.466 --> 39:47.428
<i>♪ </i>

39:47.472 --> 39:50.475
Make the right choice, Jake.

39:50.518 --> 39:53.347
Kill the bitch
before she kills you.

39:54.783 --> 39:57.003
- I don't know
if I can do that.

39:58.744 --> 40:01.703
- Man the fuck up.

40:01.747 --> 40:04.837
<i>♪ </i>

40:04.880 --> 40:07.056
What did they all do tonight?

40:07.100 --> 40:10.451
They laughed,
just like Lexy wanted.

40:10.495 --> 40:13.323
They were all laughing at you.

40:13.367 --> 40:15.064
I told you,

40:15.108 --> 40:18.807
I'm the only real friend
you got in the whole world.

40:18.851 --> 40:25.727
<i>♪ </i>

40:35.345 --> 40:38.653
Take the knife, Jake.

40:38.697 --> 40:40.568
You know you want to.

40:42.527 --> 40:44.050
Take it.

40:44.093 --> 40:50.970
<i>♪ </i>

40:57.759 --> 41:00.501
Congrats, kid.
[laughs]

41:00.545 --> 41:02.503
You're going to the Super Bowl.

41:02.547 --> 41:05.506
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:05.550 --> 41:07.639
<i>♪ </i>

41:07.682 --> 41:10.598
<i>[playful spooky music]</i>

41:10.642 --> 41:17.518
<i>♪ </i>
